children.subject: Either way you don't have much time to "late P/NP" so you gotta decide quick..

history.content:
Assuming you're in L&S, the deadline for the late change of schedule petition was last Friday. Unless you have had some extreme circumstances (health issue, family circumstances, things beyond your control, etc.), I don't think it's likely you'll be able to P/NP it this late, sorry. 

If you're not L&S I'm not sure what the process is, marking as unresolved so OP can mark it themselves.

Hello,

I'm an undergraduate and I signed up for a rather difficult graduate course. I'm pretty near the bottom of the curve so based on past grade distributions, I'll probably get a B/B+. I was thinking of P/NP-ing the course but I'm not sure what will look worse to graduate schools. I realize this is a pretty niche question but i'm wondering if anyone has any advice/dealt with a similar situation.
history.subject: Late P/NPing a Grad Class
